{"body": "<code>either?</code> doesn't sit well with me. When I read \"either\" I think \"this or that\" and not \"this or that or that or that or .... or that\".\n\n<code>within()?</code> is nice but <code>without?()</code> doesn't feel right.\n\nI'd rather write <code>!\"foo\".within?(\"a\",\"b\")</code> than <code>\"foo\".without?(\"a\",\"b\")</code>", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/981780", "created_at": "2011-04-11T01:12:11Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/258#issuecomment-981780", "updated_at": "2011-04-11T01:17:57Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 258, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/glongman", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/4e5b0563705d77ab1d3ba63f302e9148?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F016b388b5ee40f99cc161d3aeb35b545.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman/received_events", "gravatar_id": "4e5b0563705d77ab1d3ba63f302e9148", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "glongman", "type": "User", "id": 39729, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/glongman/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52386422bd3543c1510125a8"}, "id": 981780, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/258"}
